Uses of Class
org.apache.freemarker.core.Version

  • Packages that use Version 
    Package Description
    org.apache.freemarker.core
    The most commonly used API-s of FreeMarker; start with Configuration (see also the Getting Stared in the Manual.)
    org.apache.freemarker.core.model.impl
    Data model and template language type system: Standard implementations.
    org.apache.freemarker.servlet
    Servlet for legacy "Model 2" frameworks that allows using FreeMarker templates instead of JSP as the MVC View (see in the Manual), also custom JSP tag support.

      Version TopLevelConfiguration.getIncompatibleImprovements()
      Returns the value of the "incompatible improvements" setting; this is the FreeMarker version number where the not 100% backward compatible bug fixes and improvements that you want to enable were already implemented.
      protected Version Configuration.ExtendableBuilder.getRemovalVersionForUnknownSetting(String name) 
      protected Version MutableParsingAndProcessingConfiguration.getRemovalVersionForUnknownSetting(String name) 
      protected Version MutableProcessingConfiguration.getRemovalVersionForUnknownSetting(String name)
      If a setting name is unknown because it was removed over time (not just renamed), then returns the version where it was removed, otherwise returns null.
      static Version Configuration.getVersion()
      Returns the FreeMarker version information, most importantly the major.minor.micro version numbers; do not use this for #incompatibleImprovements value, use constants like Configuration.VERSION_3_0_0 for that.
